  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\nThe ChugSplash CLI tool is the last piece in the ChugSplash puzzle. This tool needs to compose all of the features we've built to make ChugSplash possible. The tool only needs to have a single command for this ticket: `chugsplash deploy`. This command takes the following arguments:\r\n\r\n- `node endpoint`\r\n- `deployer address`\r\n- `private key`\r\n- `github url`\r\n- `commit hash or tag`\r\n- `build command`\r\n- `path to contract artifacts`\r\n- `path to chugsplash config file`\r\n\r\nWe then need to use these parameters to perform the following actions:\r\n\r\n1. Connect to `node endpoint`\r\n2. Connect to `deployer address`\r\n3. Create a wallet instance with `private key`\r\n4. Clone `github url`\r\n5. Check out `commit hash or tag`\r\n6. Run `build command`\r\n7. Extract artifacts from `path to contract artifacts`\r\n8. Extract config file from `path to chugsplash config file`\r\n9. Use config file and artifacts to build the chugsplash upgrade bundle\r\n10. Wait for the bundle to be approved\r\n11. Execute each action in the bundle\r\n\r\nWe should take care to design this tool so that steps [1-9] can easily be extracted and reused for other ChugSplash-related tasks (e.g., generating bundle parameters to sign).\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\n\r\nFirst iteration is described in https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/708, which we're pivoting from since ChugSplash is moving into its own package. \r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nRe-using code from https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/855\r\n",
